<main>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Artifact Overview: SYLTrack (Mobile Application)</h2>
    <p>
      SYLTrack is a mobile application designed to help users track weight entries and measure progress toward goals over time.
      The application supports weight entry management and dashboard-style summaries to help users stay consistent.
      I selected this artifact for CS 499 because it demonstrates complete software engineering practices in a real-world style application,
      including multi-screen navigation, maintainable architecture, and scalable data handling.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Category:</strong> Software Design and Engineering</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Why This Artifact Is Included</h2>
    <p>
      I included SYLTrack in my ePortfolio because it reflects professional software development beyond basic functionality.
      The enhancement process demonstrates that I can evaluate an existing codebase, identify design issues, and implement improvements
      that increase maintainability, scalability, and usability. The artifact also aligns closely with real-world expectations of software
      products where iterative improvements and long-term structure matter.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Skills Demonstrated</h2>
    <div>
      <span class="badge">Mobile App Architecture</span>
      <span class="badge">Navigation & User Flow</span>
      <span class="badge">Maintainability</span>
      <span class="badge">Scalability</span>
      <span class="badge">Data Handling</span>
    </div>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Architecture + scalability:</strong> enhancements prioritized a stable and extensible foundation.</li>
      <li><strong>Dashboard creation:</strong> implemented a centralized dashboard (SYLBoard) for improved usability.</li>
      <li><strong>Consistent navigation:</strong> added a persistent bottom navigation bar to improve user flow.</li>
      <li><strong>User-focused structure:</strong> improved data handling so weight entries are tied to authenticated users.</li>
      <li><strong>Goal + progress support:</strong> persistently stored goals and surfaced summary data to provide insight.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="small-note">
      These improvements support clean software design principles such as separation of concerns and maintainable structure.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Enhancement Summary (Milestone Two)</h2>
    <p>
      For Milestone Two, I intentionally prioritized software engineering quality over visual branding. The enhancement work focused on
      improving architecture, navigation consistency, and data handling for scalability. These updates improved usability and created a
      more stable base that can support future enhancements.
    </p>

    <p>
     
  </div>

